<subSubSection id="00E4655CBE736232FF514BE5FCDBA2FE" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph id="484136D7BE736232FF514BE5FCDBA2FE" blockId="4.[192,785,354,506]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
The male of this species is larger than the female of 
<taxonomicName id="8FFE4D54BE736232FF714BC4FEA4A2BE" authorityName="Caldwell" authorityYear="1952" box="[224,366,419,442]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Krisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="7A8AEAC5BE736232FF714BC4FF38A2BE" box="[224,242,419,442]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7A8AEAC5BE736232FE934BC4FEA4A2BE" box="[258,366,419,442]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so it is not likely that this is the male of that species, as males are usually smaller than the females. It appears to be a valid species.
</paragraph>
